top.value: Contribution to development of peaceful and democratic Nepal with social justice for all through consolidation of the peace process.

The rights of indigenous peoples as defined in the ILO convention 169 and the Law 1257 of Bolivia are applied in the framework of democratisation and poverty reduction, through mainstreaming, land titling, and management capacity of their land.

Support to the Implementation of the HIV/AIDS National Strategy with focus on capacity building in the areas monitoring, planning and operational research. Support to multisectoral approaches in the areas for youth and orphans.

The programme aims to improve the access to justice in Bolivia through a dual strategy: On one side increasing the supply-side of public service, and on the other side enhancing the institutionalization of the sector as such.

The programme aims at supporting the modernization of the public sector at central as well as decentralised levels. In addition it provides continued support to the governments fight against corruption from 2009
The objective is to increase the capacity of the judicial system in order to improve the accessibilty of the judicial system.

To provide basic health services in accordance to geographical conditions, which are of acceptable standards, affordable and sustainable and with focus of those most at risk and responsive to the needs of citizens

The purpose of the component is to enable 5 poor provinces to better target and utilise resources to achieve Public Administration Reform results that enable more sustainable and equitable socio-economic development.
